      <description>Back by popular demand! Smokin Hit SongWriters at the Smoke House on Monteagle Mountain! Get up close and personal with mega hit SongWriters and Music Industry pros. March 18th, 19th and 20th! Sign up online at: www.SmokinHitSongWriters.com Registration is only $150.00 for a 3 day seminar and retreat! Spend the weekend in a wonderful creative [...]&lt;img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=crossharpchronicles.wordpress.com&amp;amp;blog=4569314&amp;amp;post=4979&amp;amp;subd=crossharpchronicles&amp;amp;ref=&amp;amp;feed=1" width="1" height="1" /&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/blues-in-a-digital-age/Blues_In_A_Digital_Age-Dont_Miss_The_Best_Songwriter__Music_Biz_Seminar_Reatreat_of_2011.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Back by popular demand! Smokin Hit SongWriters at the Smoke House on Monteagle Mountain!  Get up close and personal with mega hit SongWriters and Music Industry pros. March 18th, 19th and 20th!  Sign up online at: www.SmokinHitSongWriters.com Registration is only $150.00 for a 3 day seminar and retreat!</p>
<p><span id="more-4979"></span></p>
<p>Spend the weekend in a wonderful creative place network, shake hands, learn for the major music industry pros and amazing song writers<br />
ask questions, be one of the 1st 30 to sign up and participate in a open mic. Songwriting contest for a chance to co-write with a mega hit song writer.</p>
<p>Participates 30 -100 can submit a record song also for a co- writer opportunity of a life time!</p>
<p>Learn, listen and hang out with some of Nashville&#8217;s most successful songwriters<br />
Dave Gibson, Chris Wallin and Wynn Varble<br />
Have had songs Recorded By</p>
<p>Steve Wariner, Alabama, Joe Diffie, , Kenny Chesney, , Keith Anderson, Sammy Kershaw, Michael Peterson, Jeffrey Steele, Confederate Railroad, Neal McCoy, Darryl Worley, Brian McComas, and Brad Paisley, , Lee Ann Womack, Brad Paisley, , Jason Sellers, Gary Allan, Trace Adkins, Clint Daniels, Kevin Denney, Tracy Byrd, The Kinleys, Chris LeDoux, Danni Leigh, Mark Chesnutt and Sammy Kershaw, Toby Keith, Trace Adkins,Kelli Pickler, Willie Nelson, Garth Brooks and many more.<br />
This guys have had multiple number ones and award nominations</p>
<p>We got Relation ship building. Networking Clinic 101, Hear it from recording artist point of view and inside the record biz with with Nashville&#8217;s Music Business pros</p>
<p>Marla Sitten is the Director of RadioActive Promotions and President &amp; Host of Nashville Music Space with Marla Sitten.<br />
She is well known as a Nashville publicist, journalist and music industry insider. Her network of friends and colleagues is legendary. She is a one-of-a-kind dot connector and business-deal facilitator as well as a profile-builder in the entertainment community.</p>
<p>Daisy Dern graduated from the precious Berkley School of music in Boston, is a former Mercury records recording artist she is currently the Creative Director of Savannah Music Group, Inc., a grass roots independent record label and publishing company on Nashville&#8217;s Music Row, which she founded in 2008 with her husband, songwriter/artist, Dave Gibson.</p>
<p>We are very excited to add Bob Saporiti to the Music Industry panel. Bob worked for more than 20 years at Warner Bros. Records (retired) as Senior Vice- President and General manager. Bob has worked with 100&#8242;s of stars and he has worked more than 100 number 1 records. Bob now spends his time mentoring and developing young talent and writing songs. He is a full time consultant for Savannah Music Group and Voyage &#8212; Air Guitars.</p>
<p>Don&#8217;t you dare miss this great Songwriting/ and Music Business seminar retreat March 18th, 19th and 20th ant Jim Oliver&#8217;s Smoke House&#8230;Monteagle, Tennessee</p>
<p>Check it out and sign up online at: www.Smokin HitSnogWriters.com!</p>
<p>Yea only $150 does not include food or lodging&#8230;but they got special rates for that too.</p>
<p>www.SmokinHitSongWriters.com</p>
